50:56.466 --> 50:57.647
Well, I do too.

50:57.747 --> 51:07.879
In fact, I have started, and I'm now, from my syndication, I'm doing a monthly children's book column just about children's books of what I'm defined as.

51:08.019 --> 51:15.467
But I am treating them as books to be reviewed on their merits, on their terms, as writing.

51:15.487 --> 51:16.989
That would be historical breakthrough.

51:17.109 --> 51:22.455
And I've already got major newspapers that are picking it up because there's nothing else quite like it.

51:22.739 --> 51:24.541
And I'm bringing everything I have to bear.

51:24.561 --> 51:26.163
Do you realize that it is a breakthrough?

51:26.183 --> 51:29.247
That when I fought for years, I don't fight for more.

51:29.327 --> 51:30.569
I'll send you a couple.

51:30.589 --> 51:31.710
I've done six now.

51:31.870 --> 51:33.312
I do eight books a month each one.

51:33.332 --> 51:35.034
I give each one like 200 words.

51:35.054 --> 51:36.076
That's a lot of words.

51:36.977 --> 51:46.048
For a book that's only 32 pages long in some instances, I go into the writing, I go into the story, the originality of the story, the artwork, what the artwork's trying to do.

51:46.488 --> 51:50.974
If it's politically correct, basically I'm not interested in it, unless...

51:51.663 --> 51:57.068
I mean, if this is trying to make a politically correct statement, that's not interesting to me anymore.

51:57.088 --> 51:58.169
Well, to kids or to anybody.

51:59.531 --> 52:11.362
Children are offended by that, to be treated as receptacles for pure morality tales, and for how to be a good little boy or a good little girl.

52:11.723 --> 52:15.686
It doesn't work anyway, because they're all turning out to be bad little boys and bad little girls.

52:15.787 --> 52:19.290
Did you see the article in the New York Times, which I thought was like

52:20.452 --> 52:28.199
A Magna Carta of degeneracy is about two weeks ago why children's movies don't make it.

52:28.239 --> 52:38.448
And it's because Hercules and a few other children's movies that came out had not been that successful financially.

52:39.349 --> 52:49.598
And the people at Disney and the other people involved whose movies had not been successful said, I guess there's no such thing as a children's movie because we made our attempt

52:49.831 --> 52:51.454
Children aren't what they used to be.

52:51.995 --> 52:53.097
Children are barbaric.

52:53.939 --> 52:54.921
Boys are degenerates.

52:54.941 --> 52:55.482
They come in.

52:55.522 --> 52:56.123
They're monsters.

52:56.163 --> 52:57.145
They want to see killing.

52:57.165 --> 52:57.786
They want to see this.

52:58.327 --> 53:00.110
Who has made them this way?

53:00.171 --> 53:05.921
They've been looking at shitty, corrupt movies and television for so long, and now it's a kids' forum.

53:06.322 --> 53:11.552
So these studios have to conform to the new degenerate needs of American children.

53:11.853 --> 53:14.177
I could not believe this.

53:14.257 --> 53:15.038
I'll do a search.

53:15.058 --> 53:16.661
There's no irony in the situation.

53:17.362 --> 53:18.404
None whatsoever.

53:18.704 --> 53:19.786
Totally.

53:19.806 --> 53:22.230
They didn't make the money.

53:23.171 --> 53:27.138
Okay, let's have more dinosaur movies where little girls are eating up for lunch or brunch.

53:27.799 --> 53:28.781
Especially little girls.

53:28.801 --> 53:31.064
The whole thing would have girls are of no use.

53:31.084 --> 53:33.388
If a girl's in the movie, forget it.

53:33.408 --> 53:37.074
No money, because no little boy is going to go see a little girl in a movie.

53:37.094 --> 53:38.316
They actually said that.

53:39.595 --> 53:42.858
setting up the kids for just what they wanted to do.

53:44.160 --> 53:52.649
And I thought, the irony of the situation, I've been saying for 30 or more years, there's no such thing as a children's book, there's no such thing as a children's movie.

53:53.009 --> 53:53.870
Now they're saying it.

53:54.251 --> 53:58.495
But look at the reasons why they're saying it, and look at the reasons why I said it.

53:59.136 --> 54:01.779
And it's depressing.

54:02.499 --> 54:04.962
But your point is, a point is,

54:05.988 --> 54:09.733
You refuse to insult the intelligence of the reader.

54:10.655 --> 54:12.918
They say, well, your books are scary.

54:14.801 --> 54:16.703
Maybe it's too scary for some kids.

54:17.765 --> 54:32.586
And you respond by saying, you love the instance when a child is free to make any choice that he wants to make, she wants to make, and to see the consequences of that.

54:32.836 --> 54:35.840
You know, rub two sticks together and see what kind of sparks fly.

54:35.920 --> 54:38.584
I guess maybe it's kind of like... Exactly, and let them go.

54:39.405 --> 54:43.111
I can't tell you how many... I got a degree at Yale.

54:44.593 --> 54:45.594
A lot of kids came over.

54:47.056 --> 54:48.859
Wow, first saw your book.

54:49.039 --> 54:50.221
I was really scared.

54:50.661 --> 54:51.603
And I really love it.

54:51.623 --> 54:55.228
And you see the time that it takes to get involved into a work of art.

54:56.029 --> 54:56.770
Okay, that's great.

54:58.973 --> 55:00.075
I'm sorry, go ahead.

55:00.095 --> 55:00.215
No.

55:00.235 --> 55:00.295
No.

55:02.300 --> 55:04.744
Your father used to read to you, I guess, scary things?

55:05.285 --> 55:06.007
He never read.

55:06.047 --> 55:06.748
He made them up.

55:07.389 --> 55:08.130
They were petrified.

55:09.012 --> 55:10.034
These were all invented stories.

55:10.074 --> 55:11.176
These were all invented stories.

55:11.396 --> 55:12.899
He couldn't read English.

55:13.139 --> 55:14.983
They got that wrong on the net.

55:15.183 --> 55:16.966
No, they got a lot of things wrong on the net.

55:17.527 --> 55:18.729
In fact, the net is wrong.

55:20.132 --> 55:21.895
You should talk about that.

55:22.516 --> 55:25.178
Just today's paper, there's Kurt Vonnegut.

55:25.279 --> 55:25.659
I love it.

55:25.699 --> 55:26.520
I clipped it already.

55:26.540 --> 55:27.661
It's already in my file.

55:27.741 --> 55:28.502
It's hilarious.

55:28.602 --> 55:30.243
It's exactly what's going to happen.

55:30.383 --> 55:30.724
I have.

55:30.904 --> 55:33.246
I'm going to do a chapter on books.

55:33.266 --> 55:34.187
Books of the future.

55:35.348 --> 55:36.869
And, you know, the consequences.

55:37.190 --> 55:39.832
The fact that you can go in and fuck around with these things.

55:39.872 --> 55:40.413
Completely.

55:40.493 --> 55:41.394
Anything you like.

55:41.634 --> 55:43.456
And attribute it to somebody, you know.

55:43.696 --> 55:46.498
I'm getting tons of boxes saying, please autograph these books.

55:47.579 --> 55:48.821
What the fuck are these coming from?

55:49.341 --> 55:50.022
You track it down.

55:50.142 --> 55:51.443
On the internet, there's somebody.

55:51.693 --> 55:58.744
who, for a dollar, will send you the personal phone number and address of any artist you like that you want to have autographed.

55:58.764 --> 55:59.525
I have no control.

55:59.545 --> 56:00.767
I can't stop this man.

56:01.468 --> 56:05.233
Somebody, we read wild things on the Internet, the whole text.

56:06.295 --> 56:06.675
Really?

56:06.715 --> 56:11.763
I just obliterated from my consciousness.

56:11.783 --> 56:17.271
But even more threatening, of course, is the fact that people can vote.

56:17.311 --> 56:18.493
There's no guarantee...

56:19.604 --> 56:22.808
that the integrity of something that somebody... That's whatsoever.

56:23.069 --> 56:28.797
His Vonnegut... His own wife... Comments are being attributed to him that he didn't make.

56:28.857 --> 56:29.157
That's right.

56:29.177 --> 56:30.639
And there's nothing he can do to stop it.

56:30.659 --> 56:30.860
Nothing.

56:30.980 --> 56:32.242
It's all over the world.

56:33.083 --> 56:35.606
And really, it's going to take... It's a small thing.

56:36.047 --> 56:37.930
But it could be something very significant.

56:37.970 --> 56:39.051
It's a cute little remark.

56:39.332 --> 56:40.253
But let's say it wasn't.

56:40.513 --> 56:41.615
Let's say it was a slander.

56:41.795 --> 56:47.583
What if I hurt somebody or destroy somebody's life or career or throw somebody to suicide?

56:47.763 --> 56:48.885
And there were no editors...

56:48.950 --> 56:51.793
There are no filters that this stuff is going through.

56:52.614 --> 56:57.460
You just hear these schmucks on television talking about the virtues of this and the future.

56:57.500 --> 56:59.523
Again, the golden age coming, right?

56:59.643 --> 57:05.930
Well, they have a department at Brown University, which I'm going to get into, this interactive fiction workshop.

57:05.970 --> 57:11.937
Bob Cooper is running it, where you start a novel and somebody else, the reader, can play with it.

57:11.958 --> 57:17.224
And I wonder if people will be able to fool around with your pictures, for instance.

57:17.244 --> 57:17.404
Why not?

57:17.519 --> 57:19.121
They're already fully around my pictures.

57:19.562 --> 57:22.066
You can get any picture of mine you like on the internet.

57:22.086 --> 57:24.109
You can tattoo it on your back, on your ass.

57:24.369 --> 57:25.551
Anything you like.

57:25.852 --> 57:26.793
I have no control.

57:26.813 --> 57:28.596
I cannot fight anymore.

57:28.936 --> 57:31.660
You used to sue somebody for not asking permission.

57:31.700 --> 57:32.341
Forget it.

57:32.982 --> 57:39.111
But I mean, even worse than that, they can manipulate the actual artwork, the image itself.

57:39.252 --> 57:46.142
What I do is, like a lot of people of my age,

57:47.472 --> 57:50.055
I retreat from the entire situation.

57:50.996 --> 57:51.617
I retreat.

57:52.358 --> 57:54.260
I don't want to have anything to do with it.

57:55.101 --> 57:56.082
I don't want to get email.

57:57.144 --> 57:58.705
I don't want to know nothing about computers.

57:59.306 --> 58:02.250
I don't give a flying fuck about the whole thing.

58:02.270 --> 58:02.810
I'm lucky.

58:03.331 --> 58:06.855
I can sit with my Shakespeare at my keys and draw my pictures.

58:07.035 --> 58:09.959
It is mine, too.

58:09.979 --> 58:11.801
It's so virile, isn't it?

58:11.821 --> 58:14.024
I love it.

58:14.044 --> 58:15.085
I love it.

58:15.105 --> 58:16.787
Thank you.

58:17.037 --> 58:18.319
It's just how I feel.

58:18.339 --> 58:20.001
It's a privilege I've earned.

58:20.462 --> 58:21.323
I can afford it.

58:21.484 --> 58:25.870
I can afford to turn my back on this cockamamie crap culture we're living in.

58:26.331 --> 58:28.795
Fuck everybody.

58:29.796 --> 58:32.780
But your father did... These were stories that he made up.

58:32.801 --> 58:33.722
These were stories he made up.

